(What this application does) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 486 Tm
(City Air Tracker is a small batch data pipeline plus a read-only dashboard.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 441 Tm
(At a high level, the application:) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 396 Tm
(1. Reads a list of cities from `configs/cities.csv`.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 366 Tm
(2. Converts each city into latitude and longitude using the OpenWeather geocoding API.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 336 Tm
(3. Downloads historical air-pollution measurements for each city from OpenWeather.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 306 Tm
(4. Stores the API responses as raw JSON files.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 276 Tm
(5. Transforms those raw files into a cleaner analytical dataset in Parquet format.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 246 Tm
(6. Optionally publishes the same data to PostgreSQL.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 216 Tm
(7. Displays the final dataset in a Streamlit dashboard.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 171 Tm
(This is an ETL-style workflow:) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 126 Tm
(- Extract means reading data from external systems.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 96 Tm
(- Transform means reshaping and enriching that data.) Tj
ET
endstream
